affic PCAP generator\n37:   - Function: `create_basic_http_pcap(output_path)`\n38:   - Packets: HTTP GET request + HTTP response\n39:   - Output: `test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap`\n40:   - Verify: `python sample_pcap.py` generates file > 0 bytes\n41: \n42: - [ ] **T2.3** Implement DNS queries PCAP generator\n43:   - Function: `create_dns_queries_pcap(output_path)`\n44:   - Packets: DNS queries (example.com, google.com) + responses\n45:   - Output: `test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap`\n46:   - Verify: Generated PCAP contains DNS layers\n47: \n48: - [ ] **T2.4** Test sample generation\n49:   - Command: `cd sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer && python sample_pcap.py`\n50:   - Verify: Both `basic_http.pcap` and `dns_queries.pcap` exist\n51:   - Verify: Files can be read by wireshark/tcpdump\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## Phase 3: PCAP Analyzer Core Implementation\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T3.1** Create pcap_analyzer.py main script\n58:   - File: `sdk-python/examples/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n59:   - Imports: os, sys, json, logging, pathlib, typing, agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\n60:   - Verify: File exists with correct structure\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T3.2** Implement PcapAnalyzer class initialization\n63:   - Class: `PcapAnalyzer`\n64:   - Method: `__init__(router_url, workload_manager_url, auth_token, verbose)`\n65:   - Initialize: `CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"pcap-analyzer\")`\n66:   - Set paths: `remote_pcap_dir`, `remote_results_dir`, `remote_analyzer_script`\n67:   - Verify: Class can be instantiated\n68: \n69: - [ ] **T3.3** Implement setup_environment method\n70:   - Method: `setup_environment()`\n71:   - Commands: `mkdir -p` for directories, `pip install scapy --quiet`\n72:   - Verify: Sandbox directories created and scapy installed\n73: \n74: - [ ] **T3.4** Implement upload_pcap method\n75:   - Method: `upload_pcap(local_path) -> str`\n76:   - Validation: Check file exists\n77:   - Upload: `client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n78:   - Verify: `client.list_files()` shows uploaded file\n79: \n80: - [ ] **T3.5** Implement create_analyzer_script method\n81:   - Method: `create_analyzer_script()`\n82:   - Script content: `analyze_pcap(pcap_path)` function\n83:   - Features: Protocol detection (TCP/UDP/OTHER), IP extraction, port extraction, DNS query extraction\n84:   - Write: `client.write_file(script_content, remote_analyzer_script)`\n85:   - Verify: Script exists in sandbox\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T3.6** Implement analyze_pcap method\n88:   - Method: `analyze_pcap(remote_pcap_path) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n89:   - Execute: `client.run_code()` with analyzer script\n90:   - Download: `client.download_file(output_path, local_path)`\n91:   - Return: Parsed JSON results\n92:   - Error handling: CommandExecutionError, DataPlaneError\n93:   - Verify: Returns correct analysis results\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T3.7** Implement close method\n96:   - Method: `close()`\n97:   - Action: `client.stop()`\n98:   - Verify: Session properly cleaned up\n99: \n100: ---\n101: \n102: ## Phase 4: CLI & Entry Point\n103: \n104: - [ ] **T4.1** Implement command-line argument parsing\n105:   - Function: `main()`\n106:   - Arguments: `pcap_file` (positional), `--router-url`, `--workload-manager-url`, `--auth-token`, `-v/--verbose`, `--generate-samples`\n107:   - Epilog: Usage examples\n108:   - Verify: `python pcap_analyzer.py --help` shows all arguments\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T4.2** Implement main execution flow\n111:   - Flow: Check generate-samples → Validate file → Initialize analyzer → Setup → Create script → Upload → Analyze → Print results\n112:   - Output: JSON formatted results\n113:   - Verify: Complete flow executes without errors\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T4.3** Implement error handling\n116:   - Exceptions: FileNotFoundError, CommandExecutionError, DataPlaneError, generic Exception\n117:   - Finally block: Call `analyzer.close()`\n118:   - Verify: Errors are caught and logged appropriately\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Phase 5: Testing & Validation\n123: \n124: - [ ] **T5.1** Test sample generation\n125:   - Command: `python sample_pcap.py`\n126:   - Verify: Two PCAP files created in test_pcaps/\n127:   - Verify: Files are valid PCAP format\n128: \n129: - [ ] **T5.2** Test basic HTTP PCAP analysis\n130:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap`\n131:   - Verify: Output contains `total_packets: 2`\n132:   - Verify: Output contains `protocols: {TCP: 2}`\n133:   - Verify: Output contains IP addresses\n134: \n135: - [ ] **T5.3** Test DNS PCAP analysis\n136:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/dns_queries.pcap`\n137:   - Verify: Output contains `protocols: {UDP: ...}`\n138:   - Verify: Output contains `dns_queries: [\"example.com\", \"google.com\"]`\n139: \n140: - [ ] **T5.4** Test error handling - missing file\n141:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py nonexistent.pcap`\n142:   - Verify: FileNotFoundError is raised and logged\n143: \n144: - [ ] **T5.5** Test verbose mode\n145:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py test_pcaps/basic_http.pcap -v`\n146:   - Verify: DEBUG level logs are displayed\n147: \n148: - [ ] **T5.6** Test generate-samples flag\n149:   - Command: `python pcap_analyzer.py --generate-samples`\n150:   - Verify: Samples generated and analyzed in one run\n151: \n152: - [ ] **T5.7** Test missing ROUTER_URL\n153:   - Command: Unset ROUTER_URL and run analyzer\n154:   - Verify: Appropriate error message displayed\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## Phase 6: Acceptance Verification\n159: \n160: - [ ] **T6.1** Verify all spec requirements (delta-spec-ar-037.md)\n161:   - [ ] PCAP file parsing with scapy\n162:   - [ ] Protocol statistics (TCP/UDP/OTHER)\n163:   - [ ] IP address statistics (source/destination)\n164:   - [ ] Port statistics (TCP/UDP)\n165:   - [ ] DNS query extraction\n166:   - [ ] AgentCube SDK integration (CodeInterpreterClient)\n167:   - [ ] CLI argument parsing\n168:   - [ ] JSON output format\n169:   - [ ] Error handling\n170:   - [ ] requirements.txt exists\n171: \n