{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892788716,"sessionID":"ses_2848b18cfffeWmNOVf9YHBoqfg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b756233001ykzp5z4OZHZgLF","messageID":"msg_d7b754ddd001JnJ5xLMZGhcCim","sessionID":"ses_2848b18cfffeWmNOVf9YHBoqfg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c04d886dc58840aa8c4ea5e6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n2: \n3: - **Module**: docs\n4: - **Language**: TypeScript\n5: - **Size**: M\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Initialize a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project.\n\n(End of file - total 9 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n- **Module**: docs\n- **Language**: TypeScript\n- **Size**: M\n\n## Summary\n\nInitialize a Docusaurus-based documentation site framework for the agentcube project.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/spec.md","time":{"start":1775892788699,"end":1775892788715}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892788719,"sessionID":"ses_2848b18cfffeWmNOVf9YHBoqfg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b7564a3001GQDzjsGIAtVufy","messageID":"msg_d7b754ddd001JnJ5xLMZGhcCim","sessionID":"ses_2848b18cfffeWmNOVf9YHBoqfg","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_24774a044cd447aa8e6ade3e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the technical implementation of a Docusaurus v3-based documentation site for the AgentCube project. The documentation framework provides a unified, maintainable, and extensible platform for technical documentation with support for versioning, internationalization (i18n), search, and automated deployment.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Component Structure\n10: \n11: ```\n12: docs/\n13: ├── .gitignore                        # Git ignore for build artifacts\n14: ├── README.md                         # Documentation for working with docs\n15: ├── package.json                      # NPM dependencies and scripts\n16: ├── tsconfig.json                     # TypeScript configuration\n17: ├── docusaurus.config.ts              # Docusaurus site configuration\n18: ├── sidebars.ts                       # Documentation sidebar configuration\n19: ├── docs/                             # Markdown documentation files\n20: │   ├── intro/                        # Introduction documents\n21: │   ├── concepts/                     # Core concepts\n22: │   ├── crd-reference/                # CRD API reference\n23: │   ├── api-reference/                # REST API reference\n24: │   ├── sdk-cli/                      # SDK and CLI usage\n25: │   ├── deployment/                   # Deployment guides\n26: │   ├── configuration/                # Configuration reference\n27: │   ├── observability/                # Monitoring and logging\n28: │   ├── troubleshooting/              # FAQ and troubleshooting\n29: │   ├── requirements/                 # Architecture requirements (AR-001 ~ AR-042)\n30: │   └── contributing/                 # Contribution guidelines\n31: ├── src/                              # Custom React components\n32: │   ├── components/                   # Reusable components\n33: │   │   ├── CRDTable/                 # CRD field table component\n34: │   │   └── ArchitectureDiagram/      # Architecture diagram component\n35: │   ├── css/                          # Custom CSS styles\n36: │   │   └── custom.css\n37: │   └── pages/                        # Custom pages\n38: │       └── index.tsx                 # Home page\n39: ├── static/                           # Static assets\n40: │   ├── img/                          # Images and logos\n41: │   │   └── logo.svg\n42: │   ├── favicon.ico\n43: │   └── robots.txt\n44: └── i18n/                             # Internationalization (future)\n45:     ├── zh/                           # Chinese (default)\n46:     └── en/                           # English (future)\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Integration Points\n50: \n51: - **GitHub Pages**: Automated deployment via GitHub Actions\n52: - **Algolia DocSearch**: Full-text search integration (optional)\n53: - **GitHub Discussions**: Community links in navigation\n54: - **Volcano Project**: Reference documentation and branding alignment\n55: \n56: ## Data Structures\n57: \n58: ### Docusaurus Config (`docusaurus.config.ts`)\n59: \n60: ```typescript\n61: interface Config {\n62:   title: string;                      // Site title: \"AgentCube\"\n63:   tagline: string;                    // Site description\n64:   favicon: string;                    // Path to favicon\n65:   url: string;                        // Production URL\n66:   baseUrl: string;                    // Base path: \"/agentcube/\"\n67:   organizationName: string;           // GitHub org: \"volcano-sh\"\n68:   projectName: string;                // GitHub repo: \"agentcube\"\n69:   onBrokenLinks: 'throw' | 'warn';    // Link validation behavior\n70:   onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'throw' | 'warn';\n71:   \n72:   i18n: {\n73:     defaultLocale: string;            // \"zh\"\n74:     locales: string[];                // [\"zh\", \"en\"]\n75:     localeConfigs: Record<string, {\n76:       htmlLang: string;\n77:       label: string;\n78:     }>;\n79:   };\n80:   \n81:   presets: [\n82:     '@docusaurus/preset-classic',\n83:     {\n84:       docs: DocsOptions;\n85:       blog: false;\n86:       theme: ThemeOptions;\n87:     }\n88:   ];\n89:   \n90:   themeConfig: {\n91:     navbar: NavbarConfig;\n92:     footer: FooterConfig;\n93:     prism: PrismConfig;\n94:     algolia?: AlgoliaConfig;\n95:   };\n96: }\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Package Dependencies (`package.json`)\n100: \n101: ```json\n102: {\n103:   \"name\": \"agentcube-docs\",\n104:   \"version\": \"0.2.0\",\n105:   \"private\": true,\n106:   \"scripts\": {\n107:     \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n108:     \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n109:     \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n110:     \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\",\n111:     \"typecheck\": \"tsc\"\n112:   },\n113:   \"dependencies\": {\n114:     \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.6.0\",\n115:     \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.6.0\",\n116:     \"@mdx-js/react\": \"^3.0.0\",\n117:     \"clsx\": \"^2.1.0\",\n118:     \"prism-react-renderer\": \"^2.3.0\",\n119:     \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n120:     \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\"\n121:   },\n122:   \"devDependencies\": {\n123:     \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.6.0\",\n124:     \"@docusaurus/tsconfig\": \"^3.6.0\",\n125:     \"@docusaurus/types\": \"^3.6.0\",\n126:     \"typescript\": \"~5.3.3\"\n127:   },\n128:   \"engines\": {\n129:     \"node\": \">=18.0\"\n130:   }\n131: }\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ### Sidebar Configuration (`sidebars.ts`)\n135: \n136: ```typescript\n137: interface SidebarsConfig {\n138:   tutorialSidebar: SidebarItem[];\n139: }\n140: \n141: type SidebarItem = \n142:   | SidebarCategory\n143:   | SidebarDoc\n144:   | SidebarLink;\n145: \n146: interface SidebarCategory {\n147:   type: 'category';\n148:   label: string;\n149:   link?: {\n150:     type: 'doc';\n151:     id: string;\n152:   };\n153:   items: string[];\n154: }\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### Custom Component Props\n158: \n159: ```typescript\n160: // CRDTable Component\n161: interface CRDTableProps {\n162:   crdName: string;\n163:   fields: FieldSpec[];\n164: }\n165: \n166: interface FieldSpec {\n167:   name: string;\n168:   type: string;\n169:   required: boolean;\n170:   description: string;\n171: }\n172: \n173: // ArchitectureDiagram Component\n174: interface ArchitectureDiagramProps {\n175:   src: string;\n176:   alt: string;\n177: }\n178: ```\n179: \n180: ## API Contracts\n181: \n182: ### NPM Scripts\n183: \n184: | Script | Command | Description | Exit Code |\n185: |--------|---------|-------------|-----------|\n186: | `start` | `docusaurus start` | Start dev server at localhost:3000 | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n187: | `build` | `docusaurus build` | Generate static build into `build/` | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n188: | `serve` | `docusaurus serve` | Serve production build locally | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n189: | `deploy` | `docusaurus deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages | 0 on success, 1 on error |\n190: | `typecheck` | `tsc` | Type-check TypeScript files | 0 if no errors, 1 on errors |\n191: \n192: ### Configuration Validation\n193: \n194: ```typescript\n195: // docusaurus.config.ts validation\n196: const config: Config = {\n197:   // Required fields\n198:   title: 'AgentCube',                    // Must be non-empty string\n199:   tagline: 'Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration for AI agents',\n200:   url: 'https://volcano-sh.github.io',   // Must be valid URL\n201:   baseUrl: '/agentcube/',                // Must start and end with /\n202:   organizationName: 'volcano-sh',        // GitHub organization\n203:   projectName: 'agentcube',              // GitHub repository\n204:   \n205:   // Optional but recommended\n206:   onBrokenLinks: 'throw',                // Fail build on broken links\n207:   onBrokenMarkdownLinks: 'warn',\n208:   \n209:   // i18n configuration\n210:   i18n: {\n211:     defaultLocale: 'zh',\n212:     locales: ['zh', 'en'],\n213:   },\n214: };\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ### Deployment Workflow\n218: \n219: ```yaml\n220: # GitHub Actions: .github/workflows/docs.yml\n221: name: Deploy Documentation\n222: on:\n223:   push:\n224:     branches: [main]\n225:     paths: ['docs/**']\n226:   workflow_dispatch:\n227: \n228: jobs:\n229:   deploy:\n230:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n231:     defaults:\n232:       run:\n233:         working-directory: ./docs\n234:     steps:\n235:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n236:       - name: Setup Node.js\n237:         uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n238:         with:\n239:           node-version: '18'\n240:           cache: 'npm'\n241:           cache-dependency-path: docs/package-lock.json\n242:       - name: Install dependencies\n243:         run: npm ci\n244:       - name: Build documentation\n245:         run: npm run build\n246:       - name: Deploy to GitHub Pages\n247:         uses: peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v4\n248:         with:\n249:           github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n250:           publish_dir: ./docs/build\n251: ```\n252: \n253: ## Error Handling\n254: \n255: ### Build Errors\n256: \n257: | Error | Source | CLI Output | Resolution |\n258: |-------|--------|------------|------------|\n259: | Broken links | Markdown links to non-existent files | `Error: Broken link to ./missing.md` | Fix or remove broken link |\n260: | Missing sidebar item | Sidebar references non-existent doc | `Error: Sidebar item not found: intro/missing` | Add doc or update sidebar |\n261: | TypeScript errors | Invalid config types | `TS2322: Type '...' is not assignable` | Fix type mismatch |\n262: | Missing dependencies | package.json not installed | `Error: Cannot find module '@docusaurus/core'` | Run `npm install` |\n263: | Node version mismatch | Node < 18 | `Error: Node.js 18+ required` | Upgrade Node.js |\n264: \n265: ### Runtime Errors (Dev Server)\n266: \n267: | Error | Source | CLI Output | Resolution |\n268: |-------|--------|------------|------------|\n269: | Port in use | localhost:3000 occupied | `Error: Port 3000 is already in use` | Use different port or kill process |\n270: | Invalid MDX | Malformed MDX syntax | `SyntaxError: Unexpected token` | Fix MDX syntax |\n271: | Missing import | Import path doesn't exist | `Error: Cannot find module './Component'` | Fix import path |\n272: \n273: ### Deployment Errors\n274: \n275: | Error | Source | GitHub Actions Output | Resolution |\n276: |-------|--------|----------------------|------------|\n277: | Build timeout | Build > 10 minutes | `Error: The operation was canceled` | Optimize build, check for infinite loops |\n278: | Permission denied | GitHub token issue | `Error: Permission denied` | Check repository permissions |\n279: | Disk space | Insufficient runner disk space | `Error: No space left on device` | Clean up build artifacts |\n280: \n281: ### Error Boundaries\n282: \n283: ```typescript\n284: // Custom error boundary for React components\n285: import React from 'react';\n286: \n287: export class ErrorBoundary extends React.Component<\n288:   {children: React.ReactNode},\n289:   {hasError: boolean}\n290: > {\n291:   constructor(props: {children: React.ReactNode}) {\n292:     super(props);\n293:     this.state = {hasError: false};\n294:   }\n295: \n296:   static getDerivedStateFromError() {\n297:     return {hasError: true};\n298:   }\n299: \n300:   render() {\n301:     if (this.state.hasError) {\n302:       return <div>Component failed to load</div>;\n303:     }\n304:     return this.props.children;\n305:   }\n306: }\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ## Testing Strategy\n310: \n311: ### Unit Tests\n312: \n313: **File**: `docs/src/components/__tests__/`\n314: \n315: | Test Case | Component | Description |\n316: |-----------|-----------|-------------|\n317: | `TestCRDTable_RendersFields` | CRDTable | Verify all fields render correctly |\n318: | `TestCRDTable_RequiredIndicator` | CRDTable | Verify required fields show ✅ |\n319: | `TestArchitectureDiagram_AltText` | ArchitectureDiagram | Verify alt text is accessible |\n320: | `TestArchitectureDiagram_ImageSrc` | ArchitectureDiagram | Verify image source is correct |\n321: \n322: ```typescript\n323: // Example: CRDTable test\n324: import React from 'react';\n325: import {render} from '@testing-library/react';\n326: import {CRDTable} from '../CRDTable';\n327: \n328: describe('CRDTable', () => {\n329:   it('renders all fields correctly', () => {\n330:     const fields = [\n331:       {name: 'image', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Container image'},\n332:       {name: 'command', type: 'string[]', required: false, description: 'Command'},\n333:     ];\n334:     \n335:     const {getByText} = render(\n336:       <CRDTable crdName=\"AgentRuntime\" fields={fields} />\n337:     );\n338:     \n339:     expect(getByText('image')).toBeInTheDocument();\n340:     expect(getByText('string')).toBeInTheDocument();\n341:     expect(getByText('Container image')).toBeInTheDocument();\n342:   });\n343: });\n344: ```\n345: \n346: ### Integration Tests\n347: \n348: **File**: `docs/__tests__/integration/`\n349: \n350: | Test Case | Description |\n351: |-----------|-------------|\n352: | `TestBuild_Success` | Production build completes without errors |\n353: | `TestDevServer_Start` | Development server starts on localhost:3000 |\n354: | `TestNavigation_Links` | All sidebar links navigate correctly |\n355: | `TestSearch_Functionality` | Search returns expected results (if Algolia configured) |\n356: | `TestMobile_Responsive` | Site is responsive on mobile viewports |\n357: \n358: ```bash\n359: # Integration test script\n360: #!/bin/bash\n361: set -e\n362: \n363: echo \"Running integration tests...\"\n364: \n365: # Test 1: Build succeeds\n366: echo \"Testing build...\"\n367: npm run build\n368: if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then\n369:   echo \"❌ Build failed\"\n370:   exit 1\n371: fi\n372: echo \"✅ Build succeeded\"\n373: \n374: # Test 2: Serve works\n375: echo \"Testing serve...\"\n376: npm run serve &\n377: SERVE_PID=$!\n378: sleep 5\n379: curl -s http://localhost:3000 > /dev/null\n380: if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then\n381:   echo \"❌ Serve failed\"\n382:   kill $SERVE_PID\n383:   exit 1\n384: fi\n385: kill $SERVE_PID\n386: echo \"✅ Serve succeeded\"\n387: \n388: # Test 3: Links are valid\n389: echo \"Testing links...\"\n390: npm run build -- --skip-build\n391: # Use link checker tool\n392: echo \"✅ Links valid\"\n393: \n394: echo \"All integration tests passed!\"\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ### Visual Regression Tests\n398: \n399: **Tool**: Playwright or Percy (optional)\n400: \n401: ```typescript\n402: // Example: Playwright visual test\n403: import {test, expect} from '@playwright/test';\n404: \n405: test('homepage should match screenshot', async ({page}) => {\n406:   await page.goto('http://localhost:3000');\n407:   await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('homepage.png');\n408: });\n409: \n410: test('documentation page should match screenshot', async ({page}) => {\n411:   await page.goto('http://localhost:3000/docs/intro/01-overview');\n412:   await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot('docs-overview.png');\n413: });\n414: ```\n415: \n416: ### Accessibility Tests\n417: \n418: **Tool**: axe-core or Lighthouse CI\n419: \n420: ```bash\n421: # Lighthouse CI configuration\n422: # docs/.lighthouserc.json\n423: {\n424:   \"ci\": {\n425:     \"collect\": {\n426:       \"staticDistDir\": \"./build\",\n427:       \"url\": [\n428:         \"http://localhost/agentcube/\",\n429:         \"http://localhost/agentcube/docs/intro/01-overview\"\n430:       ]\n431:     },\n432:     \"assert\": {\n433:       \"assertions\": {\n434:         \"accessibility\": [\"error\", {\"minScore\": 0.9}]\n435:       }\n436:     }\n437:   }\n438: }\n439: ```\n440: \n441: ### Test Coverage Targets\n442: \n443: | Component | Coverage Target |\n444: |-----------|-----------------|\n445: | Custom React components | 90% |\n446: | Configuration files | 100% |\n447: | Documentation content | N/A (manual review) |\n448: | CI/CD pipeline | 100% (all steps must pass) |\n449: \n450: ### Test Fixtures\n451: \n452: ```typescript\n453: // docs/__fixtures__/crd-data.ts\n454: export const sampleAgentRuntimeFields = [\n455:   {name: 'image', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Container image'},\n456:   {name: 'command', type: 'string[]', required: false, description: 'Container command'},\n457:   {name: 'sessionTimeout', type: 'string', required: false, description: 'Session TTL'},\n458:   {name: 'resources', type: 'ResourceRequirements', required: false, description: 'Resource limits'},\n459: ];\n460: \n461: export const sampleCodeInterpreterFields = [\n462:   {name: 'runtime', type: 'string', required: true, description: 'Runtime type'},\n463:   {name: 'version', type: 'string', required: false, description: 'Runtime version'},\n464:   {name: 'sandbox', type: 'SandboxSpec', required: false, description: 'Sandbox configuration'},\n465: ];\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ## Implementation Details\n469: \n470: ### File Generation\n471: \n472: ```bash\n473: # Initialize Docusaurus project\n474: cd docs\n475: npx create-docusaurus@latest . classic --typescript\n476: \n477: # Install additional dependencies\n478: npm install --save-dev @docusaurus/module-type-aliases @docusaurus/tsconfig\n479: \n480: # Create directory structure\n481: mkdir -p docs/{intro,concepts,crd-reference,api-reference,sdk-cli,deployment,configuration,observability,troubleshooting,requirements,contributing}\n482: mkdir -p src/{components,css,pages}\n483: mkdir -p static/{img}\n484: mkdir -p __tests__/{unit,integration}\n485: ```\n486: \n487: ### Configuration Steps\n488: \n489: 1. **Update `docusaurus.config.ts`**:\n490:    - Set `title`, `tagline`, `url`, `baseUrl`\n491:    - Configure GitHub organization and project\n492:    - Set up i18n locales\n493:    - Configure navbar and footer\n494:    - Add Algolia search (optional)\n495: \n496: 2. **Update `sidebars.ts`**:\n497:    - Define sidebar categories\n498:    - Add document IDs in order\n499:    - Configure category links\n500: \n501: 3. **Create `package.json` scripts**:\n502:    - `start`: Development server\n503:    - `build`: Production build\n504:    - `serve`: Local production serve\n505:    - `deploy`: GitHub Pages deployment\n506: \n507: 4. **Create `.gitignore`**:\n508:    ```\n509:    node_modules/\n510:    build/\n511:    .docusaurus/\n512:    *.log\n513:    ```\n514: \n515: ### Custom Component Implementation\n516: \n517: #### CRDTable Component\n518: \n519: ```typescript\n520: // src/components/CRDTable/index.tsx\n521: import React from 'react';\n522: import styles from './styles.module.css';\n523: \n524: interface FieldSpec {\n525:   name: string;\n526:   type: string;\n527:   required: boolean;\n528:   description: string;\n529: }\n530: \n531: interface CRDTableProps {\n532:   crdName: string;\n533:   fields: FieldSpec[];\n534: }\n535: \n536: export function CRDTable({crdName, fields}: CRDTableProps) {\n537:   return (\n538:     <div className={styles.crdTable}>\n539:       <h3>{crdName}</h3>\n540:       <table>\n541:         <thead>\n542:           <tr>\n543:             <th>Field</th>\n544:             <th>Type</th>\n545:             <th>Required</th>\n546:             <th>Description</th>\n547:           </tr>\n548:         </thead>\n549:         <tbody>\n550:           {fields.map((field) => (\n551:             <tr key={field.name}>\n552:               <td><code>{field.name}</code></td>\n553:               <td><code>{field.type}</code></td>\n554:               <td>{field.required ? '✅' : '❌'}</td>\n555:               <td>{field.description}</td>\n556:             </tr>\n557:           ))}\n558:         </tbody>\n559:       </table>\n560:     </div>\n561:   );\n562: }\n563: \n564: export default CRDTable;\n565: ```\n566: \n567: ```css\n568: /* src/components/CRDTable/styles.module.css */\n569: .crdTable {\n570:   margin: 2rem 0;\n571:   overflow-x: auto;\n572: }\n573: \n574: .crdTable table {\n575:   width: 100%;\n576:   border-collapse: collapse;\n577: }\n578: \n579: .crdTable th,\n580: .crdTable td {\n581:   padding: 0.75rem;\n582:   border: 1px solid var(--ifm-color-emphasis-300);\n583: }\n584: \n585: .crdTable th {\n586:   background-color: var(--ifm-color-emphasis-100);\n587:   font-weight: bold;\n588: }\n589: \n590: .crdTable code {\n591:   font-size: 0.9em;\n592: }\n593: ```\n594: \n595: #### ArchitectureDiagram Component\n596: \n597: ```typescript\n598: // src/components/ArchitectureDiagram/index.tsx\n599: import React from 'react';\n600: import styles from './styles.module.css';\n601: \n602: interface ArchitectureDiagramProps {\n603:   src: string;\n604:   alt: string;\n605: }\n606: \n607: export function ArchitectureDiagram({src, alt}: ArchitectureDiagramProps) {\n608:   return (\n609:     <div className={styles.diagramContainer}>\n610:       <img src={src} alt={alt} className={styles.diagram} />\n611:     </div>\n612:   );\n613: }\n614: \n615: export default ArchitectureDiagram;\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ### Documentation Content Structure\n619: \n620: Each documentation category follows a consistent structure:\n621: \n622: ```markdown\n623: ---\n624: sidebar_label: Overview\n625: title: AgentCube Overview\n626: description: Introduction to AgentCube\n627: ---\n628: \n629: # AgentCube Overview\n630: \n631: ## What is AgentCube?\n632: \n633: [Content here]\n634: \n635: ## Key Features\n636: \n637: | Feature | Description |\n638: |---------|-------------|\n639: | Feature 1 | Description |\n640: \n641: ## Architecture\n642: \n643: ```\n644: [Architecture diagram]\n645: ```\n646: \n647: ## Quick Links\n648: \n649: - [Link 1](./doc2.md)\n650: - [Link 2](../other/doc.md)\n651: ```\n652: \n653: ### Versioning Strategy (Future)\n654: \n655: ```typescript\n656: // docusaurus.config.ts versioning\n657: presets: [\n658:   [\n659:     'classic',\n660:     {\n661:       docs: {\n662:         sidebarPath: './sidebars.ts',\n663:         versions: {\n664:           current: {\n665:             label: 'v0.2.x (Development)',\n666:           },\n667:           '0.1.x': {\n668:             label: 'v0.1.x (Stable)',\n669:           },\n670:         },\n671:         showLastUpdateTime: true,\n672:         showLastUpdateAuthor: true,\n673:       },\n674:     },\n675:   ],\n676: ],\n677: ```\n678: \n679: ### Internationalization Strategy (Future)\n680: \n681: ```typescript\n682: // docusaurus.config.ts i18n\n683: i18n: {\n684:   defaultLocale: 'zh',\n685:   locales: ['zh', 'en'],\n686:   localeConfigs: {\n687:     zh: {\n688:       htmlLang: 'zh-CN',\n689:       label: '简体中文',\n690:     },\n691:     en: {\n692:       htmlLang: 'en-US',\n693:       label: 'English',\n694:     },\n695:   },\n696: },\n697: ```\n698: \n699: ## Dependencies\n700: \n701: ```json\n702: {\n703:   \"runtime\": {\n704:     \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.6.0\",\n705:     \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.6.0\",\n706:     \"@mdx-js/react\": \"^3.0.0\",\n707:     \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n708:     \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\"\n709:   },\n710:   \"dev\": {\n711:     \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.6.0\",\n712:     \"@docusaurus/tsconfig\": \"^3.6.0\",\n713:     \"@docusaurus/types\": \"^3.6.0\",\n714:     \"typescript\": \"~5.3.3\",\n715:     \"@testing-library/react\": \"^14.0.0\",\n716:     \"@playwright/test\": \"^1.40.0\"\n717:   },\n718:   \"optional\": {\n719:     \"@docusaurus/plugin-content-blog\": \"^3.6.0\",\n720:     \"@docusaurus/plugin-ideal-image\": \"^3.6.0\",\n721:     \"@easyops-cn/docusaurus-search-local\": \"^0.40.0\"\n722:   }\n723: }\n724: ```\n725: \n726: ## File Structure\n727: \n728: ```\n729: agentcube/\n730: ├── docs/\n731: │   ├── .gitignore                    # Git ignore for build artifacts\n732: │   ├── README.md                     # Documentation for working with docs\n733: │   ├── package.json                  # NPM dependencies and scripts\n734: │   ├── package-lock.json             # Locked dependency versions\n735: │   ├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript configuration\n736: │   ├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus site configuration\n737: │   ├── sidebars.ts                   # Documentation sidebar configuration\n738: │   ├── docs/\n739: │   │   ├── intro/\n740: │   │   │   ├── _category_.json       # Category configuration\n741: │   │   │   ├── 01-overview.md        # Introduction documentation\n742: │   │   │   ├── 02-features.md        # Features documentation\n743: │   │   │   └── 03-quickstart.md      # Quick start guide\n744: │   │   ├── concepts/\n745: │   │   │   ├── _category_.json\n746: │   │   │   ├── 01-agent-runtime.md\n747: │   │   │   ├── 02-code-interpreter.md\n748: │   │   │   └── 03-router.md\n749: │   │   ├── crd-reference/\n750: │   │   │   ├── _category_.json\n751: │   │   │   ├── agent-runtime.md\n752: │   │   │   └── code-interpreter.md\n753: │   │   └── requirements/\n754: │   │       ├── _category_.json\n755: │   │       ├── ar-001.md\n756: │   │       └── ar-002.md\n757: │   ├── src/\n758: │   │   ├── components/\n759: │   │   │   ├── CRDTable/\n760: │   │   │   │   ├── index.tsx\n761: │   │   │   │   └── styles.module.css\n762: │   │   │   └── ArchitectureDiagram/\n763: │   │   │       ├── index.tsx\n764: │   │   │       └── styles.module.css\n765: │   │   ├── css/\n766: │   │   │   └── custom.css\n767: │   │   └── pages/\n768: │   │       └── index.tsx\n769: │   ├── static/\n770: │   │   ├── img/\n771: │   │   │   ├── logo.svg\n772: │   │   │   └── favicon.ico\n773: │   │   └── robots.txt\n774: │   ├── __tests__/\n775: │   │   ├── unit/\n776: │   │   └── integration/\n777: │   └── scripts/\n778: │       └── check-ar-docs.sh            # AR documentation coverage checker\n779: └── .github/\n780:     └── workflows/\n781:         └── docs.yml                    # GitHub Actions deployment\n782: ```\n783: \n784: ## Environment Configuration\n785: \n786: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n787: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n788: | `NODE_ENV` | No | `development` | Environment mode (`development` or `production`) |\n789: | `PORT` | No | `3000` | Development server port |\n790: | `ALGOLIA_APP_ID` | No | - | Algolia application ID |\n791: | `ALGOLIA_API_KEY` | No | - | Algolia search API key |\n792: | `ALGOLIA_INDEX_NAME` | No | - | Algolia index name |\n793: \n794: ## Regeneration\n795: \n796: If Docusaurus version updates are needed:\n797: \n798: ```bash\n799: # Update Docusaurus to latest version\n800: cd docs\n801: npm update @docusaurus/core @docusaurus/preset-classic\n802: \n803: # Verify build still works\n804: npm run build\n805: \n806: # Check for breaking changes in changelog\n807: # https://docusaurus.io/releases\n808: ```\n809: \n810: ## Security Considerations\n811: \n812: 1. **Dependency Updates**: Regularly update Docusaurus and dependencies to patch security vulnerabilities\n813: 2. **Content Security Policy**: Configure CSP headers for production deployment\n814: 3. **XSS Prevention**: Sanitize any user-generated content in MDX components\n815: 4. **API Key Protection**: Never commit Algolia API keys to repository; use GitHub Secrets\n816: \n817: ## Performance Optimization\n818: \n819: 1. **Image Optimization**: Use WebP format and lazy loading for images\n820: 2. **Code Splitting**: Docusaurus automatically code-splits by route\n821: 3. **Tree Shaking**: Ensure custom components are tree-shakeable\n822: 4. **Cache Strategy**: Configure proper caching headers for static assets\n823: 5. **Build Time**: Monitor build time; optimize if > 2 minutes\n824: \n825: ## Accessibility\n826: \n827: 1. **Semantic HTML**: Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)\n828: 2. **Alt Text**: All images must have descriptive alt text\n829: 3. **Keyboard Navigation**: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard-accessible\n830: 4. **Color Contrast**: Meet WCAG AA contrast requirements\n831: 5. **Screen Reader Support**: Test with screen readers (NVDA, VoiceOver)\n832: \n833: ## Monitoring and Analytics\n834: \n835: 1. **Google Analytics**: Optional integration via Docusaurus plugin\n836: 2. **Broken Link Monitoring**: Run link checker in CI/CD\n837: 3. **Build Performance**: Track build times in GitHub Actions\n838: 4. **User Feedback**: Add feedback widget (optional)\n839: \n840: ## Future Enhancements\n841: \n842: 1. **Blog Section**: Enable Docusaurus blog for release announcements\n843: 2. **Versioning**: Implement full versioning for multiple releases\n844: 3. **Interactive Examples**: Add CodeSandbox or StackBlitz embeds\n845: 4. **API Playground**: Integrate Swagger UI for API testing\n846: 5. **Community Translations**: Enable community-contributed translations\n\n(End of file - total 846 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation of a Docusaurus v3-based documentation site for the AgentCube project. The documentation framework provides a unified, maintainable, and extensible platform for technical documentation with support for versioning, internationalization (i18n), search, and automated deployment.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── .gitignore                        # Git ignore for build artifacts\n├── README.md                         # Documentation for working with docs\n├── package.json                      # NPM dependencies and scripts\n├── tsconfig.json                     # TypeScript configuration\n├── docusaurus.config.ts              # Docusaurus site configuration\n├── sidebars.ts                       # Documentation sidebar configuration\n├── docs/                             # Markdown documentation files\n│   ├── intro/                        # Introduction documents","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-042/design.md","time":{"start":1775892788705,"end":1775892788716}}}}
